The paper deals with population protocols and their variations, which are models of distributed computing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also involves the computation of predicates and the use of identifiers, which are topics related to algorithms and data structures, respectively. Hence, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also a likely category. The paper also discusses the space complexity of the protocols, which falls under the category of cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The use of identifiers and their limitations is a topic related to information theory, which is covered by cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of the power of the protocols, which can be considered a topic related to social networks, covered by cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
